# data-models

## Core Entities and Relationships (Score: 95/100)

### Transaction Model
- Links payment activities to booth rentals and stylists
- Maintains status tracking through payment lifecycle
- Supports multiple payment methods (ACH, Card, PayPal)
- Records transaction dates and amounts
- Associates validation states per payment type

### Booth Rental Model
- Implements dual pricing structures:
  - Fixed weekly rate
  - Percentage-based revenue sharing
- Tracks rental status (Active/Inactive)
- Links to associated stylist records
- Maintains payment history and due dates

### Stylist Model
- Connected to booth rentals and transactions
- Records payment history and preferences
- Tracks revenue for percentage-based calculations
- Maintains status based on payment records

### Payment Status Model
- Specialized states per payment method:
  - ACH: Pending→Processed→Complete
  - Card: Authorized→Complete
  - PayPal: Initiated→Redirected→Complete
- Propagates status changes to related entities
- Tracks payment verification states

### Rent Calculation Model
- Handles both fixed and percentage-based calculations
- Stores calculation parameters and history
- Links revenue data for dynamic adjustments
- Maintains preview calculations for estimates

